<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="differentiating diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Differentiating diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Easily to separate from other Chinese species because of the largely glabrous basal cell of fore wing, combined with dark brown scutellum, less slender hind basitarsus and lesser body size (length of fore wing not exceeding 3 mm).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
